        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A form of peeling skin syndrome characterized by a generalized distribution. It comprises two sub-types: the non-inflammatory (PSS type A) and the inflammatory (PSS type B) form. PSS type A is characterized by generalized white scaling with superficial non-inflammatory peeling of the skin while PSS type B is characterized by superficial patchy peeling of the entire skin with underlying erythroderma pruritus and atopy."
        },
